    "en": "Representations with prime conditions",
    "ja": null,
    "latex": "The predicate that `n` can be written as $x + y$ with $x, y > 0$ such that both\n$x + ny$ and $x^2 + ny^2$ are prime. -/\ndef HasPrimeRepresentation (n : ℕ) : Prop :=\n  ∃ x y : ℕ, 0 < x ∧ 0 < y ∧ n = x + y ∧ (x + n * y).Prime ∧ (x ^ 2 + n * y ^ 2).Prime\n\n@[category test, AMS 11]\ntheorem hasPrimeRepresentation_2 : HasPrimeRepresentation 2 :=\n  ⟨1, 1, by norm_num, by norm_num, by norm_num, by norm_num",
